Title : Kimberly Stevenson
Text : {{Orphan|date=July 2014}}

{{Infobox person
|name        = Kimberly "Kim" Stevenson
|image       = 
|nationality = American
|education   = 
|occupation  = Senior Vice President and General Manager of [[Lenovo]] }}

'''Kimberly Stevenson''' is a Senior Vice President and General Manager for Data Center Infrastructure at [[Lenovo]].<ref name="Bloomberg">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=109840927&capId=410120&previousCapId=4090682&previousTitle=Hugh%20Johnson%20Advisors%20LLC |title=Kimberly S. Stevenson: Executive Profile & Biography |author=<!--Not stated--> |website=[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]] |access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref>

Prior to joining Lenovo, Kim spent five years at [[Intel]], most recently as chief operating officer ([[Chief operating officer|COO]]) for the Client, Internet of Things and System Architecture (CISA) Group.<ref name="Bloomberg"/> Prior to that, she was Intel's chief information officer ([[Chief information officer|CIO]]). Before Intel, she held a variety of positions at [[Electronic Data Systems|EDS]], including vice president of its worldwide communications, media and entertainment (CM&E) industry practice, as well as vice president of enterprise service management,<ref name="Bloomberg"/> where she oversaw the global development and delivery of enterprise services.

Before EDS, Kim spent 18 years at [[IBM]]<ref name="BW">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180723005089/en/Skyworks-Appoints-Kimberly-Stevenson-Board-Directors |title=Skyworks Appoints Kimberly Stevenson to its Board of Directors |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=July 23, 2018 |publisher=[[Business Wire]] |access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref> in several executive positions including Vice President of Marketing and Operations of the eServer iSeries division. She also has served on the board of directors of [[Cloudera]] and [[Riverbed Technology]]<ref name="BW"/> and is currently serving on the board of Boston Private Financial Holdings, Inc. and [[Skyworks Solutions]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.everythingrf.com/News/details/6556-Skyworks-Appoints-Kimberly-Stevenson-to-its-Board-of-Directors |title=Skyworks Appoints Kimberly Stevenson to its Board of Directors  |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=July 24, 2018 |work= |publisher=everything RF |access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref>

Stevenson won numerous awards including [[Silicon Valley Business Journal]]'s Best CIOan Evanta Top 10 Breakaway Leader, ''[[Huffington Post]]'''s Most Social CIO as well as the CIO 100 award by [[CIO.com]] for four years in a row.{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} She was named the Woman of Excellence Digital Trailblazer by the National Association of Female Executives ([[NAFE]]).{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} In 2015, she won the ''[[Forbes]]'' CIO Innovation Award.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/peterhigh/2018/06/25/lenovo-gm-kim-stevensons-journey-from-cio-to-innovating-for-them/ |title=Lenovo GM Kim Stevenson's Journey From Being A CIO To Innovating For Them |last=High |first=Peter |date=June 25, 2018 |publisher=[[Forbes]] |access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref>

Kim earned a bachelor's degree from [[Northeastern University]] and holds a master's degree in Business Administration from [[Cornell University]].<ref name="Bloomberg"/> In her free time, Kim is an avid tennis player and enjoys kayaking and paddle boarding.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}

